snippet.textDisplay: A couple of years ago, part of the research I was doing for a book project, I was watching The Story of China with Michael Wood. Something that caught my eye without looking for it, I noticed how most people in the background, in the streets, that were incidentally appearing on camera, hundreds of them, were smiling. I told someone, things cannot be as bad as we are told they are in China when people display such a natural radiant energy. In New York, you can sense how the stress weights heavily on most everyone shoulders. Nobody smiles either.

snippet.textDisplay: Ah finally! Finally, the episode I have been waiting for so so much!! Ever since you mentioned in a comment that you are already in Chongqing and meeting Alex in the afternoon, I just couldn't wait for the episode to come out! Really can't express how eager I was so see you exploring Chongqing! I have lived in China for 2 years and have been to the city. But I visited the city during summer and did not enjoy much because it's incredibly hot during the day. However, it's the night view of the city that blew me off to the river. It's literally a cyberpunk city and it was overwhelming for me. Everything was so lit up, entire skyscrapers looking like a video screen! I couldn't stop looking everywhere! I was in such awe!!! Cant wait for the next episode!!! And once again, the music simply pumps up the mood and you look so gorgeous in that traditional dress! Love from India.
